Full Title: 9th International Conference on South Asian Languages 
Short Title: ICOSAL-9 

Date: 07-Jan-2010 - 09-Jan-2010
Location: Patiala (Punjab), India 
Contact Person: Joga Singh
Meeting Email: jogasinghvirk@yahoo.co.in
Web Site: http://icosal.ning.com/notes/ICOSAL-9 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; General Linguistics; Sociolinguistics 

Call Deadline: 30-Oct-2009 

Meeting Description:

9th International Conference on South Asian Languages
January 7, 2009 to January 9, 2009

The ICOSAL-9 is open for general linguistics and language sessions. The
Conference also proposes to hold Panel Discussion on important themes of
contemporary relevance. 

Please see http://icosal.ning.com/notes/ICOSAL-9 for more information. 

Call for Papers:

Research papers in all aspects of Linguistics with special reference to South
Asian Languages - phonetics, phonology, morphology, syntax, semantics,
pragmatics, semiotics,  typology, historical linguistics and language change,
language politics, sociolinguistics, psycho-linguistics, neuro-linguistics,
discourse analysis, language technologies & computational linguistics, language
education, language planning, geolinguistics, language ecology, clinical
linguistics, translation studies, field linguistics, lexicography, cognitive
science, literacy studies and literary theories - are invited  for presentation
and discussion. If you wish to hold a Panel Discussion, please let us know the
Theme of the Panel and the proposed names of the panelists.

Abstract:

Abstracts of research papers in not more than 300 words typed in double space
A-4 size paper with an extra page, if needed, for references, may be submitted
to the undersigned as per schedule given below. The abstract should, on the top,
contain information with regard to specific session in which it is intended to
be presented. 
 
Last date for submitting the Abstract: October 30, 2009
Communication regarding acceptance of the Abstract: November 15, 2009  
Submission of Paper: December 15, 2009. 
 
It will be very helpful if a copy of the abstract/ paper is sent in MS Word by
e-mail.

Registration Fee:

Indian and Russian delegates: Rs. 500/-
Other Foreign delegates: US. $ 100/- (students will pay half of this amount)
Local delegates and Students: Rs.200/-
 
Registration fee may be paid in the form of a demand draft drawn in favour of
the Head, Department of Linguistics and Punjabi Lexicography payable at State
Bank of Patiala, Punjabi University Branch, Patiala, India. Registration fee can
be paid in cash at the time of Registration for conference at the venue.
 
Weather:

Weather in Patiala is generally cold ( 5-10 degree Celsius)  during the 1st 
half of the month of January.   Woolen clothes would be needed.
 
Accommodation:

Free accommodation and hospitality will be provided by the organizers in the
University Guest Houses /hostels. 

Contact for Information and Registration:

